   "description": {
    "en": "The Minimum Assessment Scope rules help providers define assessment boundaries narrowly enough to avoid unnecessary review of components that do not affect the offering's security. These rules still ensure the assessment includes the resources and connections needed to understand the offering's confidentiality, integrity, and availability."
